TN Beverages has partnered with the National Association of Primary Heads (Naph) to establish Premier Plus Mahewu Under-14 Schools Soccer Tournament. BY GARISH PHIRI The partnership will see the company pouring a $100 000, which will be used to run the tournament. In a statement, TN beverages director, Tawanda Nyambirai said the company will pour in the money to enhance the development of the game at grassroots level. “We have committed to sponsor Naph for a period of two years; to the tune of $100 000 in the launch and operation of an Under-14 soccer tournament,” he said. “In line with our corporate social responsibility strategy, we believe in giving back to the community that supports us through nurturing and promoting young talent in sports and arts.”
The tournament will be officially launched in Harare tomorrow.